= Visiting Graves

*Visiting graves is divided into three categories:*

*1. Permissible (Legitimate) Visit:*

This is the type of visit that is encouraged in Islam, and it includes visiting graves:

 • To remember the Hereafter.
 
 • To greet the deceased.
 
 • To pray for them.
 

*2. Innovative (Bid‘ah) Visit:*


This type goes against the perfection of Tawḥīd and is a means leading to shirk. Examples include:

 • Intentionally worshipping Allāh at the grave.
 
 • Seeking blessings from the grave.
 
 • Donating rewards of good deeds at the grave.
 
 • Traveling specifically to visit the grave.
 
 • And other similar practices.
 
*3. Visit which is shirk (Polytheism):*


This type contradicts Tawḥīd and occurs when a person directs any act of worship to the one buried in the grave. Examples include:

 • Calling upon the dead instead of Allāh.
 
 • Seeking help (isti‘ānah) or relief (istighāthah) from them.
 
 • Slaughtering animals (sacrifice) or making vows (nadhr) for them.
 
 • And other similar acts.